name: FirstBaseline
shortdesc: Starting point options for the first baseline of text.

property.name: ASCENT_OFFSET
property.shortdesc: The tallest character in the font falls below the top inset of the object.

property.name: CAP_HEIGHT
property.shortdesc: The tops of upper case letters touch the top inset of the object.

property.name: LEADING_OFFSET
property.shortdesc: The text leading value defines the distance between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the object.

property.name: EMBOX_HEIGHT
property.shortdesc: The text em box height is the distance between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the object.

property.name: X_HEIGHT
property.shortdesc: The tops of lower case letters touch the top inset of the object.

property.name: FIXED_HEIGHT
property.shortdesc: Uses the value specified for minimum first baseline offset as the distance between the baseline of the text and the top inset of the object.
